About
In the heart of the United Arab Emirates, where cultures unite, Dubai Opera stands tall, as the main lighthouse for the performing arts in the Middle East. A global stage, where artistic languages, creative expressions, from all over the world converge and blend every day. Dubai Opera serves, unifies and inspires the community of Dubai and beyond. Through excellence in the arts, Dubai Opera aims to build a more vibrant and inclusive society, placing Dubai at the forefront of the global cultural scene.
Duration: More than 3 hours

The area

Neighborhood: Downtown Dubai
You can’t fail to miss Dubai’s iconic Burj Khalifa, the world’s tallest building. It towers over the city and resides in the prestigious Downtown development. Once an old army base, Downtown is now the jewel in Dubai’s crown, a beautiful residential and leisure area housing not only the world’s tallest building, but the world’s largest fountains and mall. Wide marble sidewalks are perfect for strolling, with restaurants, art galleries and children’s play areas. Specially commissioned sculptures line the roads and Downtown is often used as a canvas for modern art displays and community events such as Classic Car Shows and National Day parades. In the cooler months, cross one of the many bridges to the Burj Khalifa park and enjoy a picnic alongside residents and visitors, or enjoy a lunch or dinner watch the dancing fountains. Because of its mixed use, Downtown is a fantastic place to mix with Dubai residents and locals and watch real life unfold in a cosmopolitan environment.

Just awful
Jan 2024 • Family
Unfortunately this place doesn’t live up to its name or expectations
We had a horrible experience, we bought a full box as we wanted to be close, we took my mother in law ( 83 years old and in wheelchair) and my father in law 91 years old
When we arrived we were shown a way to reach the box that couldn’t take my mother in law wheelchair so we had to send her back with my sister to be in the house with her, then our view from the box was just awful, more than half of the show happened from middle to back and even the projections where only partially accessible to your eyes, there was even speakers blocking the view of the floor, We had the full first half on this horrible set up then after complaining they offered us ViP ( which was too far away for my father in law ) and then a box more to the center which only improved partially the view
We complained the next day and received a call from a representative who offered us to upgrade us on future visits and the reversing on the payment but after one month with no updates we contacted again just to be told that they never do reversals and only if we purchase more tickets they would upgrade us
As we told the representative this place is basically scamming customers, they are very much aware that there is no way anyone who purchases those boxes can see this show properly, even if you push yourself to the border and twist your knees awkwardly, which as you can imagine is not ideal posture to enjoy your time, and they don’t provide fair and honest information on the accessibility for wheelchair or the actual view the guests will have from this box
This is really poor and giving a bad name for the city's attractions for no particular reason just lack of common sense and professionalism.
If you visit this place just have a selfie from the outside, save yourself the bad taste from purchasing an experience there.
